https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/9vQecfBQrti4waTujM47vttoHP9.jpg 73 Suspect Words is a deceptively simple and ultimately chilling meditation on the power of text. Ahwesh succinctly delves into one person's obsessive irrationality, and his expressions of fear and anger. Based on a spell-check of the Unabomber's manifesto, the work evokes the violence underlying the key words presented. 73 Suspect Words
